<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1428,2020]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,337,1719,1743]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
A typical member of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Gnaspini" authorityYear="1996" box="[577,893,1720,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Appadelopsis">
<emphasis box="[577,723,1720,1743]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Ptomaphagus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[740,883,1720,1743]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Appadelopsis</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[909,972,1720,1743]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1080,1104]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,386,1073]" captionTargetId="figure-192@1.[264,1323,366,1090]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ptomaphagus merritti sp. n. Dorsal habitus of the holotype." pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity box="[1137,1295,1720,1743]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="2.85" metricValueMin="2.75" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="2.8" valueMax="2.85" valueMin="2.75">2.75–2.85 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.375" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.35" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="1.375" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.35">1.35– 1.40 mm</quantity>
. Pronotum 1.72–1.78 times wider then long, 2.09–2.14 times shorter then elytra. Elytra together 1.23–1.29 times longer then wide. Aedeagus apex is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Peck)" baseAuthorityName="Peck" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[787,953,1789,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Ptomaphagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suteri">
<emphasis box="[787,874,1789,1812]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P.suteri</emphasis>
(Peck)
</taxonomicName>
, with dorsal section upturned into long, wide knob with a distinct depression in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[640,743,1824,1847]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–6" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[324,1245,1193,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-198@1.[701,1267,1193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 2–6. Genitalia of Ptomaphagus merritti sp. n. 2—aedeagus, lateral view; 3—apex of median lobe, frontal view; 4—apex of median lobe, dorso-lateral view; 5—spermatheca, dorsal view; 6—spermatheca, lateral view." pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Figs. 2–4</figureCitation>
). Edges of both dorsal and ventral sections in frontal view deeply asymmetrically sinuate (
<figureCitation box="[413,478,1858,1881]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–6" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[324,1245,1193,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-198@1.[701,1267,1193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 2–6. Genitalia of Ptomaphagus merritti sp. n. 2—aedeagus, lateral view; 3—apex of median lobe, frontal view; 4—apex of median lobe, dorso-lateral view; 5—spermatheca, dorsal view; 6—spermatheca, lateral view." pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[651,751,1858,1881]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–6" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[324,1245,1193,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-198@1.[701,1267,1193,1707]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 2–6. Genitalia of Ptomaphagus merritti sp. n. 2—aedeagus, lateral view; 3—apex of median lobe, frontal view; 4—apex of median lobe, dorso-lateral view; 5—spermatheca, dorsal view; 6—spermatheca, lateral view." pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Figs. 5–6</figureCitation>
) with sharp bend in posterior end, distinctly sinuate central section and anterior crest perpendicular to middle section.
</paragraph>
